</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FFE97619FF3AD2E84BF4F3DC" blockId="52.[145,448,1712,1734]" box="[145,448,1712,1734]" pageId="52" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFE97619FF3AD2E84AC4F3DF" box="[145,240,1712,1733]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="469">Habitat:</emphasis>
Rain forest litter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FFE97619FF3AD2AE4B41F272" blockId="52.[145,762,1782,1896]" pageId="52" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFE97619FF3AD2AE4B34F211" box="[145,256,1782,1803]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="469">Remarks:</emphasis>
Following the results of our phylogenetic analysis, this species is transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFE97619FDCDD34D48C6F230" authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1936" box="[614,754,1813,1834]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="52" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFE97619FDCDD34D48C6F230" box="[614,754,1813,1834]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="469">Callitrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a placement also consistent with the morphological traits of the species.
</paragraph>
